<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security, Civilian Committees Resume Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901103094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0915 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1901103094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Taba, 19 Jan (MENA)--The Security and Civilian 
Committees stemming from the Gaza-Jericho Committee resumed 
their meetings in Taba this morning. 
  The Security Committee is led on the Palestinian side by Dr. 
Nabil Sha'th, political adviser to Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat, and on the Israeli side by General Amnon Shahaq, 
Israeli deputy chief of staff. The Civilian Committee is 
chaired by Attorney Jamil al-Turayfi for the Palestinian side, 
while the Israeli side is chaired by Gadi Zohar, in charge of 
the civilian administration in the West Bank. 

</TEXT>

