<F P=100> Morocco </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Discusses Chemical Weapons Treaty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801200494 Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network in Arabic 
1600 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Prime Minister Mohamed Karim Lambrani today 
presided over a Council of Ministers meeting, during which a 
number of draft decrees were discussed. [passage omitted] 
  After that, the Council [of Ministers] discussed the treaty 
banning the development, production, stockpiling, and use of 
chemical weapons, along with the destruction of those weapons, 
as well as the draft law on the approval, in principle, of this 
agreement under which the signatory countries undertake not to 
develop, produce, possess, keep or transport chemical weapons, 
either directly or indirectly, under any circumstances. The 
signatory countries also undertake to destroy the chemical 
weapons they possess and accord paramount priority to ensuring 
the safety of people and the protection of the environment in 
the course of transporting, storing, or destroying these 
weapons. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

