<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Venue Reportedly Moved to al-Kufrah </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1801134994 Cairo ROSE AL-YUSUF in Arabic 17 Jan 94 p 78 </F>
<F P=103> NC1801134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo ROSE AL-YUSUF </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Libyan ministers are facing extreme hardship 
because the venue of the Libyan cabinet meetings has been moved 
to al-Kufrah, a desert region 800 km away from Tripoli. The 
ministers, who have their homes in Tripoli, are thus forced to 
remain in al- Kufrah. 
  The decision to move the venue of the cabinet meetings came 
as a punishment from al-Qadhdhafi to the ministers after Prime 
Minister Abu-zayd Durdah submitted a memorandum of reforms that 
he prepared with 'Abd-al-Salam Jallud, who has secluded himself 
in his home after al-Qadhdhafi refused to discuss the memorandum 
with him. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

