<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bashir Praises Redivision of States Project </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1801195094 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1300 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1801195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lieutenant General 'Umar al-Bashir, president of the 
Republic, has affirmed that the government is striving, with 
firm steps, towards consolidating the pillars of federal rule at 
this historic stage through which the country is passing. This 
was said when he met, in his office today at the Friendship 
Hall, a delegation from Bara Province visiting Khartoum to take 
part in the consultative meeting which convened recently between 
the president and executive and popular leaderships to discuss 
the redivision of the states. 
  Lt. Gen. al-Bashir explained to the delegation that the 
government relies upon the project for the redivision of the 
states because of the revenue that it will achieve in the field 
of development, despite its exorbitant financial cost. Lt. Gen. 
al- Bashir explained that the new states need an unleashing of 
energies and the deployment of available resources to guarantee 
the continuation of true development. He pointed out that there 
is no way of building Sudan except by self-reliance and 
concerted official and popular effort. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

