<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister on PRC Minister's Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1801193094 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1300 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1801193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Husayn Sulayman Abu-Salih, the foreign minister, 
has affirmed the importance of the visit of the Chinese 
delegation which visited the country recently led by the deputy 
chairman of the State Council and foreign minister. He noted 
that during the visit ways of strengthening bilateral relations 
and fields of bilateral and regional cooperation were discussed. 
Dr. Abu-Salih explained, at the Foreign Ministry forum today, 
that China pursues a policy of economic openness and it can find 
many opportunities for investment in Sudan in various fields. 
He explained that it contributes to many important projects in 
the country, like the Hamdab Dam project and the elevation of 
Al-Rusayris Dam and energy and irrigation projects. 
  Dr. Abu-Salih touched on the visit of the Iranian delegation 
to the country, representing the Ministry of Construction Jihad. 
He pointed out the firm cooperation between Sudan and Iran. 
  Ambassador (Mityang Malwal Mabor), director of the Peace 
Department at the Foreign Ministry and member of the 
government's delegation to the negotiations of the 
Intergovernmental Authority on Drought and Development [IGADD] 
states, which were recently held in Nairobi, also spoke at the 
information forum of the Foreign Ministry. He said that 
ministers of the four IGADD states, who had been entrusted with 
establishing peace in Sudan, had submitted their report in this 
respect to Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi. He explained that 
the Kenyan president, chairman of the IGADD committee, will hold 
consultations with the presidents of Uganda, Ethiopia, Eritrea 
and Lieutenant General 'Umar al-Bashir, president of the 
Republic, to discuss ways of establishing peace in the south of 
the country. 

</TEXT>

