<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saddam Addresses Athens Conference Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1801200194 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1900 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1801200194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Leader President Saddam Husayn, may God preserve 
him, has said that all great missions, including the roles of 
the prophets in conveying God's message to mankind, are first 
communicated to a few people and then to millions of people. 
This came during a meeting he held today with a delegation from 
the International Committee of the Athens International 
Conference on Solidarity With Iraq. The conference was held in 
Athens on 6-7 November 1993. His excellency added: What we 
should do as people -- as well as officials who are aware of 
their nation's objectives regarding human relations -- is to 
work as hard as we can to reach a sound level in terms of human 
ties and relations among nations. 
  Addressing the chairman and members of the committee, his 
excellency, may God preserve him, said: The work you are 
undertaking is considered great by almighty God and by the 
people of the world, because you are truly democratic and 
because you want to see others enjoying what you yourselves are 
enjoying. He added: Meanwhile, the others -- those who speak 
about democracy and human rights -- kill and slaughter people 
and then continue to kill people by starving them. 

</TEXT>

