<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baghdad Reopens Defense Ministry Headquarters </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1801150094 Baghdad INA in English 1400 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1801150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, Jan 18, INA--The headquarters of Iraq's 
Defence Ministry was reopened on Monday after Iraqi 
reconstruction teams have restored the historical magnificence 
of the first group of the Ministry's buildings which came under 
successive air and missiles attacks during the 1991 U.S.-led war. 
  A celebration was held at the site of the reconstructed 
premises attended by Defence Minister General 'Ali Hasan 
al-Majid, the Army chief of staff and senior Army offices. 
  The reconstruction work included the removal of 225,000 
tones 
of debris of 17 buildings. Eight new buildings were 
reconstructed in addition to over-all repair work for 11 other 
buildings which were partly damaged. 
  On January 17, 1991, the Defence Ministry headquarters came 
under air and missile attacks. It was attacked again on January 
19 and 23, complete parts of the Ministry were demolished. 
  The old buildings were replaced with new modern ones that 
have exactly the same distinct architectural features of the 
destroyed ones. 

</TEXT>

