<F P=100> Islamic Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO's 'Abd-Rabbuh Arrives for ICO Follow-Up Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1801215894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2115 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1801215894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 18 Jan (MENA)--Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, head of the 
PLO Information Department, arrived in Cairo this evening to 
attend the meetings of the ministerial follow-up committee 
formed by the second Islamic conference of the Islamic 
Conference Organization countries' information ministers. The 
committee is chaired by Information Minister Safwat al-Sharif 
and will begin its meetings in Cairo tomorrow, Wednesday. 
  'Abd-Rabbuh stated that the meeting will follow up on the 
objectives that were set during previous meetings and will work 
to bolster cooperation between the Islamic countries to serve 
their joint causes. 
  He said that convening the meetings in Cairo has a special 
significance since that city is currently the venue for meetings 
and conferences that have influence on various levels and in 
many fields. He noted that Cairo is the heart of every media 
and political activity. 
  He affirmed the interest of the Palestinian side to always 
coordinate with Egypt on all levels to achieve the necessary 
progress in the peace process. 

</TEXT>

