<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabbani Agrees to Interim Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1801162294 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 
1609 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1801162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Borhanoddin Rabbani has expressed the 
confidence that peace and normalcy will return soon to Kabul. 
According to a wireless message received in the office of 
Nangarhar Shura [council] this evening, the president told a 
group of commanders which called on him again in the outskirts 
of Kabul today that he agrees to the proposal for setting up an 
interim government. He said he was willing to sacrifice his 
office in the best interest of the Afghan nation. 
  Talking to Radio Pakistan's representative in Peshawar 
today, 
a top aide of the Afghan prime minister said that Mr. Golboddin 
Hekmatyar and the Supreme Coordination Council composing parties 
opposed to the president is prepared to work for the early 
return of peace and normalcy to Kabul. 
  Meanwhile, the chief of Hezb-e Eslami [Islamic Party of 
Afghanistan] Khales group, Mowlvi Muhammad Younes Khales, told 
Afghan Islamic Press in Peshawar that leaders of all mojahedin 
groups should sit together to find out a solution to [word 
indistinct] end crisis. 

</TEXT>

