<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hekmatyar Rejects Proposal on Mediation Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801192094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1830 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hekmatyar's Hezb-e Eslami [Islamic Party of 
Afghanistan] has rejected a plan proposed by Ahmad Shah Mas'ud, 
that suggested a 15-member council should mediate between the 
warring factions in Afghanistan. 
  According to an IRNA report, the Hezb-e Eslami spokesman 
said: Hekmatyar's Hezb-e Eslami considers this proposal as an 
effort to create a rift between Afghanistan's Jihadi groups. 
  Furthermore, the Hezb-e Wahdat-e Eslami-e [Islamic Unity 
Party of Afghanistan] spokesman in Peshawar told IRNA: The 
resolution of the Afghan problem can only be accomplished by 
agreement among the four major parties in that country; that is 
Hezb-e Eslami, Hezb-e Wahdat, Jonbesh-e Shomal [the Northern 
Movement] and Rabbani's Jami'at-e Eslami [Islamic Society of 
Afghanistan]. 

</TEXT>

