<H3> <TI>   Official Provides 6-Month Oil Revenue Figures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801182894 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1510 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Kuwait, 18 Jan (KUNA) -- The second deputy prime 
minister and minister of finance and planning Nasir al-Rawdan 
said today that oil revenues between 1 July 1993 and the end of 
last year reached 1.235 billion Kuwaiti dinars whereas nonoil 
revenues were only 166 million dinars. This came in a financial 
report, a copy of which was obtained by KUNA, which was 
presented by al-Rawdan to the National Assembly on the economic 
situation in Kuwait, on problems and challenges facing it, and 
recommondations that might boost the economy. 
  The report predicted, however, that Kuwait's oil revenues 
could be as much as 944 million dinars during the next six 
months presuming output would remain at two million barrels per 
day and at an average of $10.50 per barrel. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

