<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Addresses YSP Secretaries Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1801170594 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1500 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1801170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Summary From Poor Reception] The secretaries of the 
Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] organizations in the Yemeni 
governorates held an expanded meeting yesterday evening. 
Brother 'Ali Salim al- Bid, vice chairman of the Presidential 
Council and secretary general of the YSP, and other party 
officials attended the meeting. The conferees discussed and 
reviewed the current political developments in Yemen. 
  Brother al-Bid asserted that safeguarding Yemeni unity and 
democracy is a major task. He pointed out that the YSP will 
proceed on the path of unity and democracy and of progress for 
the Yemeni people. He urged the YSP organizations to show 
vigilance and responsibility toward the fate of the people and 
the homeland. 
  Al-Bid also expressed the YSP's conviction that the national 
dialogue can achieve its objectives. He voiced confidence that 
the Yemeni people can distinguish between one thing and another 
and know where their interest lies. Al-Bid added that our 
people are looking forward to building a modern state. 

</TEXT>

