<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saudi Border Talks Continue in Sanaa </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1901083894 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1901083894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Yemeni-Saudi joint experts committee on borders 
held the second meeting of its seventh session in Sanaa this 
evening. The seventh session began yesterday evening under 
brother Ja'far Sa'id Ba-Salih, deputy director of the 
Presidential Council Office and head of our country's side, and 
Dr. Matlab al-Nafisah, head of the experts branch at the Saudi 
Council of Ministers, who heads the fraternal Saudi side on the 
committee. 
  The committee resumed discussion of the viewpoints and 
proposals submitted by the two sides. The committee began its 
seventh session at 1900 yesterday evening, Monday. 
  The Yemeni News Agency, SABA', has learned that a cordial 
and 
fraternal atmosphere permeates this session, reflecting the 
solid fraternal relations between the two people. 

</TEXT>

