<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Confers With U.S. Ambassador in Ta'izz </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1701211294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1701211294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, received at the 
Presidential Palace in Ta'izz today Arthur Hughes, the U.S. 
ambassador to our country. 
  During the meeting, they discussed bilateral relations as 
well as the issues and developments of interest to both friendly 
countries. They also reviewed developments in our country and 
the U.S. position on them in light of the U.S. support for our 
country's unity and democracy. 
  The U.S. ambassador reaffirmed that the United States is 
interested in our country's circumvention of the current 
political crisis through peaceful dialogue and by renouncing 
violence in a way that will entrench the march of unity and 
democracy in Yemen. He pointed out that a unified Yemen is an 
important element in regional security and stability and in the 
world peace march. 
  The brother chairman of the Presidential Council expressed 
his appreciation for the positive U.S. position on developments 
in our country. He lauded the level of Yemeni-U.S. relations, 
adding that they are relations of friendship established on a 
firm basis of cooperation and common interests. He voiced 
confidence that our country will get through the current 
circumstances and challenges by constructive and responsible 
dialogue in a way that will safeguard the march of unity, 
democracy, and peace in Yemen. 
  Foreign Minister brother Muhammad Salim Basindwah attended 
the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-53730 </DOCNO>
