<H3> <TI>   Amal-Israel Clashes Occur in Southern Areas </TI></H3>
<H4>   Amal Attacks, Israeli Shelling Continue </H4>
<F P=102> NC1601104794 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 1000 
GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1601104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Israeli forces continue to besiege the townships 
of Rumaysh, 'Ayta al-Sha'b, and 'Aramta. Our correspondent 
reports that enemy forces bombarded the approaches to 
al-Nabatiyah and Kafr Tibnit with mortars. 
  Meanwhile, an Amal Movement group attacked enemy positions 
in 
Hula, using rockets and medium machine guns. A clash ensued for 
10 minutes between the group and the enemy troops. Enemy 
helicopters flew over the scene of clashes. Another group 
attacked the occupation position in al-Shumariyah, inflicting 
heavy material losses on the position. Immediately afterward, 
the enemy forces shelled Zawtar al-Sharqiyah and Zawtar 
al-Gharbiyah. 

</TEXT>

