<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Amal-Israel Clashes Occur in Southern Areas </TI></H3>
<H4>   Further on Continued Fighting </H4>
<F P=102> NC1701071794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0530 GMT 17 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1701071794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Israeli occupation forces have continued their 
attacks on villages and towns in the south. Israeli heavy 
artillery shelled Qabrikha, Wadi al-Saluqi, and the perimeters 
of the Tallusah position. This was accompanied by raking with 
machine guns. Earlier, the outskirts of al-Nabatiyah al-Fawqa 
and Kafr Tibnit came under artillery fire and raking with 
machine-gun fire. The area around Majdal Silm and Shaqra also 
came under artillery fire. Israeli helicopter gunships also 
strafed those areas. 
  The Amal Movement has announced that one of its groups has 
attacked the Israeli position on Tallusah hill, using automatic 
weapons and mortars. A 15-minute clash ensued with the 
position's guards, during which the resistance fighters scored 
direct hits and destroyed the observation tower. 

</TEXT>

