<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Amal-Israel Clashes Occur in Southern Areas </TI></H3>
<H4>   SLA Positions Shelled </H4>
<F P=102> NC1701103194 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 0945 
GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1701103194 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Our correspondent in the security strip reported 
today that an explosive device went off at 1030 today under a 
South Lebanese Army [SLA] patrol on the road to al-Shumariyah. 
At the same time, artillery fire hit the al-Shumariyah and 
al-Qantarah positions belonging to the SLA. Our correspondent 
reports that the shelling is continuing at this hour, but he did 
not report any injuries among the ranks of SLA. 
  Our correspondent reports from Tyre that the Israeli forces 
fired four mortar shells at Wadi al-Hujayr in the central 
sector. They also directed raking fire from their positions in 
al-Qantarah Wadi al-Saluqi and Wadi al-Hujayr. At around 1015 
today, Israeli warplanes broke the sound barrier over Tyre and 
the Palestinian camps. 

</TEXT>

