<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Academics Agree Syria Ready for `Egyptian Model' Peace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1501094294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 15 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1501094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Academics from Israel and Syria who met recently in 
Oslo worked out a nonbinding document of understanding which 
they have conveyed to the prime minister's bureau in Jerusalem 
and to President al-Asad's office in Damascus. Those who 
participated on the Israeli side were reserve Brigadier General 
'Amos Gilbo'a and Dr. Yosi Olmert. On the Syrian side, there 
was Professor 'Aziz Shukri, dean of the Law Faculty at the 
University of Damascus, and another professor whose name was not 
given. 
  Our correspondent Yo'el Nir reports that the document says 
that Syria agrees to peace with Israel based on the Egyptian 
model -- which includes the opening of embassies and trade, 
economic, and cultural ties -- in return for an Israeli 
withdrawal from the entire Golan Heights. Each stage in the 
normalization process will be accompanied by a withdrawal stage. 
Differences surfaced on the timeframe for the withdrawal and 
the fate of the Jewish settlements on the Golan, although the 
Syrians accepted the Israeli position that settlements should 
not be uprooted. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

