<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rothschild Named Acting Head of Talks Team in U.S. </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1801164094 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1600 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1801164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Major General Dani Rothschild, coordinator of 
government activities in the territories, was appointed acting 
head of the Israeli delegation to talks with the Palestinians in 
Washington. Our political correspondent Udi Segal reports that 
the prime minister has not yet officially ordered Rothschild to 
travel to Washington next week because he does not see a need to 
resume the talks on the Palestinian track in Washington while no 
progress is being made in Taba. 
  Rothschild was appointed after the Americans yesterday made 
clear to Rabin that they will send invitations to the 
Palestinians as well, and suggested that Nabil Sha'th and Amnon 
Shahaq also come to Washington. Jerusalem, however, does not 
wish to harm the Taba talks, which are not linked with the 
Washington talks. Rothschild was appointed acting head because 
the decision on who is to head the delegation to Washington has 
not been made yet. 

</TEXT>

