<F P=100> IRAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Afghan Foreign Minister on Need For Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901140694 Tehran IRNA in English 1225 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Jan. 19, IRNA -- The visiting Afghan Deputy 
Foreign Minister Jalil Shams here Wednesday said that recent 
clashes in Afghanistan mostly resembled a coup d'etat. The 
Afghan official is currently here for the international seminar 
on the process of development in Central Asia and the Caucasus. 
He told IRNA that incompetency of jihad groups in establishing 
order and security and improving economic and administrative 
condition had added to the people's dissatisfaction. 
  The Afghan official further noted that warring sides should 
declare ceasefire and search for solutions to their differences 
through negotiation. Otherwise, he stressed, the Afghan people 
would suffer heavy financial and human losses. He dismissed 
some analysis that the recent war had an ethnic nture and said 
it was merely a struggle for gaining power. Shams stressed the 
need for international assistance to reconstruct his 
war-devastated country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

