<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Comments on Afghan Situation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1901120694 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 
1100 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1901120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Foreign Office spokesman said in Islamabad today 
that Pakistan attaches highest priority to providing 
humanitarian assistance to displaced people in Afghanistan due 
to continued fighting. Pakistan is making comprehensive 
arrangements to provide them adequate relief in collaboration 
with United Nations and other relief organizations. The 
spokesman said the Pakistan-Afghan border has never been sealed 
since the establishment of the mojahedin government in 
Afghanistan. He said according to the latest information, 
fighting in Kabul has been continuing with low intensity due to 
inclement weather. The situation in Mazar-e Sharif is, however, 
peaceful. 

