<F P=100> IRAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rafsanjani Receives Pakistani Army Chief </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1901031294 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1901031294 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Iranian President 'Ali Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani has 
stressed the need for cooperation between Iran and Pakistan for 
the resolution of regional conflicts. During a meeting with 
visiting Pakistani Chief of Army Staff General Abdul Waheed in 
Tehran yesterday, the Iranian president highlighted the 
importance of exchanging views to find ways and means to help 
resolve the disputes in Afghanistan and occupied Kashmir. The 
Iranian president also proposed promoting bilateral economic and 
cultural ties and expanding mutual cooperation to ensure border 
security and to check narcotics smuggling. Gen. Waheed 
expressed support for Hashemi- Rafsanjani's proposal for mutual 
cooperation to ensure border security and checking narcotics 
smuggling. 

