<H3> <TI>   Two Police Officers Killed by Unidentified Assailants </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2001112094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1050 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2001112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 Jan (MENA)--Major Muhammad 'Abd-al-Hamid 
Hasan, chief of the Baqur police station, within Abu Tij center 
in Asyut Governorate, Upper Egypt, and Sergeant Major 'Antar 
Madani Muhammad were killed this morning and conscript Muhammad 
Mahrus Fath-al-Bab was wounded when unknown assailants fired on 
them. 
  Making the statement, a responsible Interior Ministry 
security source said the major and the men accompanying him were 
passing by when two unidentified assailants fired at them 
killing the major and the sergeant major and wounding the 
conscript, who was taken to Abu Tij Hospital for treatment. 
  The security source added that the Asyut security forces 
immediately went to the scene and the area is being combed to 
arrest the criminals. 
  The prosecution has been informed to start investigations. 

</TEXT>

