<H3> <TI>   Palestinians Involved in Killing Policeman Detained </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2001210994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1940 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2001210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 Jan (MENA)--The Higher State Security 
Prosecution decided today to detain terrorists 'Ali Muhammad 
Ahmad Farhan and Samir Isma'il Salih, Palestinian nationals, for 
15 days pending investigations for committing the terrorist 
crime in al-Ma'sarah yesterday morning. 
  The prosecution charged the two men with murdering Police 
Officer Sayyid 'Abd-al-Fattah Hasan, the attempted murder of 
Police Officer Khalid 'Adli, and possession of unlicensed 
firearms, explosives, and ammunition. The prosecution also 
decided to put the wounded terrorist 'Ali Muhammad Ahmad Farhan 
under guard in Qasr al-'Ayni Hospital. 
  The prosecution took statements from members of the police 
unit that was at the scene of the incident yesterday. 
  Members of the police unit also gave details about what was 
found in the apartment rented by the two suspects in 
al-Ma'sarah. Large quantities of bombs, explosives, and 
material used to manufacture explosives with the intention of 
carrying out terrorist acts and endangering security and public 
order were discovered in the apartment. 

