<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officers Resign To Protest Deteriorating Military </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2001120194 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 16 Jan 94 p 9 </F>
<F P=103> NC2001120194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Exclusive" report on the "Brothers" page] </F>
  [Text] Many Army officers tendered their resignations to 
the commander in chief of the Armed Forces last week to protest 
the deteriorating military establishment. In their resignation 
letters, the officers said they rejected a new escalation of war 
in the south and a government plan to send a military expedition 
to the south comprising nationalist officers who are not 
affiliated with the National Islamic Front. The plan is seen as 
a government attempt to liquidate these officers in war. 
  The "Brothers" learned that the commander in chief has not 
yet replied to the resignations, both because the Army needs the 
officers' expertise and because there is no cash to pay the 
allowance to which they would be entitled. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

