<H3> <TI>   Cooperation Accords Signed With Iran </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2001170494 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 0430 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2001170494 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Official discussions between Sudanese and Iranian 
officials were concluded in Khartoum yesterday. The two sides 
signed a joint communique which affirmed the depth of relations 
between Khartoum and Tehran. The communique included a number 
of new agreements in the spheres of investment, trade, economic 
cooperation and infrastructure. 
  Dr. Awad Ahmad al-Jaz, minister of presidential affairs, 
signed on behalf of the Sudanese side, while Gholam Reza 
Foruzesh, minister of construction jihad in his country, signed 
on behalf of the Iranian side. 

</TEXT>

