<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Leader Welcomes Release </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001094594 Paris Radio France International in French 0630 
GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2001094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The gates of Saharan security centers in Algeria 
have been opened; some of the 780 Islamist prisoners in these 
security centers have been released. [passage omitted] 
  A reaction from Rabah Kebir, one of the leaders of the 
Islamic Salvation Front in exile: He says these measures are 
insufficient: 
  [Begin Kebir recording] I am very pleased about the release 
of some of our brothers who were imprisoned wrongly and without 
trial in concentration camps and who have been there for two 
years now. This is not enough, however, because thousands of 
our brothers are still in prison, such as our leaders, first of 
all. 
  As for the national dialogue conference, as far as we are 
concerned, the junta in power is not to be taken seriously. 
That is why this conference has no chance of success. It is 
only a propaganda ploy to gain time. Should they ever want a 
negotiable solution, all they have to do is to look at the one 
condition we set during our news conference on 17 August 1993. 
It is no use giving us little presents to cheer us up. We are 
not children. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

