<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Saudi Arabia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemeni Border Talks End; Next Session in Apr </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001223494 Riyadh SPA in Arabic 2130 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2001223494 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riyadh, 20 Jan (SPA) -- The Saudi side in the joint 
Saudi-Yemeni border committee arrived this evening in Riyadh led 
by His Excellency Dr. Muttalib 'Abdallah al-Nafisah, chairman of 
the body of experts at the council of ministers, after the 
conclusion of the seventh round of negotiations between the two 
sides. The following joint press communique was released by the 
joint Saudi- Yemeni border committee of experts: 
  The joint Saudi-Yemeni border committee of experts held its 
seventh round in the city of Sanaa 17-20 January 1994. The 
committee resumed its deliberations about its tasks with regard 
to the borders between the two countries. A friendly and 
cordial atmosphere prevailed at the meetings. The two sides 
agreed to continue the negotiations and the discussions in a 
future meeting to be held in the city of Riyadh starting on 25 
April 1994. 
  The Saudi side to the joint Saudi-Yemeni border committee of 
experts left Sanaa for Riyadh and was seen off by the head and 
members of the Yemeni side of the committee. The Saudi side 
expressed its thanks to the head and members of the Yemeni side 
for the warm welcome and hospitality. 

</TEXT>

