<H3> <TI>   German Economics Minister Rexrodt Continues Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets GCC Secretary General </H4>
<F P=102> LD1901184494 Riyadh SPA in Arabic 1358 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riyadh, 19 Jan -- His Excellency Shaykh Fahim 
Bin-Sultan al-Qasimi, the secretary general of the Gulf 
Cooperation Council [GCC], this morning at the council 
headquarters met His Excellency Dr. Guenter Rexrodt, the German 
economics minister. 
  During the meeting, economic and trade relations between the 
two sides were discussed. Relations between the GCC states and 
the European Union, within the framework of the economic 
agreement concluded between them in 1988, and the ongoing talks 
between the GCC and the European Union on a free trade 
agreement, were also reviewed. 
  The German side heard briefing by his excellency the 
secretary general on the achievements of collective work within 
the framework of the GCC. 
  Dr. Abdullah al-Quwayz, the assistant secretary general for 
economic affairs, and a number of officials in the General 
Secretariat took part in the meeting. 

</TEXT>

