Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, returned this afternoon to 
the capital, Sanaa, following an inspection visit to the 
governorates of Ta'izz and Ibb. 
  During the visit, the chairman of the Presidential Council 
took note of citizens' affairs and of work at government 
facilities and agencies in the two governorates. He also met 
with the brother officials of executive agencies, their eminence 
the ulema, social figures, the leaders of political party and 
organization branches, and the leaders of mass, creative, and 
professional organizations. 
  He discussed with them many national issues and 
developments, 
primarily the recent developments in our country. He also spoke 
to them, stressing the need to unify all efforts and energies in 
order to shoulder responsibilities and perform tasks so our 
country can overcome all difficulties and challenges and create 
good prospects for progress and prosperity. 
  He stressed the need for making efforts to enhance national 
accord and cohesion of ranks and to advance the march of 
development to achieve our people's ambitions and hopes for 
progress and development. 
  During the visit, the chairman of the Presidential Council 
was accompanied by several officials. 

