<F P=102> JN1901143694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1901143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, received the ambassadors 
of the EC member states in Ta'izz today. They reviewed aspects 
of relations between our country and the EC member states and 
discussed developments in our country in light of the results of 
the ambassadors' previous meetings with the brother president 
and the vice president and in light of the Document of Pledge 
and Accord, worked out by the Political Forces Dialogue 
Committee to build a modern Yemeni state. 
  The ambassadors said their countries' welcomed and gave 
their 
blessings for the document as a positive step toward ending the 
crisis peacefully and achieving stability in Yemen. They also 
expressed hope that the document would be implemented 
effectively. They reaffirmed their countries' support for unity 
and democracy, their appreciation of dialogue as a basis for 
solutions, and their objection to violence and military action. 
They also said that the EC member states are eager to maintain 
fruitful cooperation and to support the march of social and 
economic development in the Republic of Yemen. 
  The meeting was attended by Foreign Minister Muhammad Salim 
Basindwah and General People's Congress member 'Abd-al-Karim al- 
Iryani. 

