<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PFLP-GC Spokesman Vows `Armed Struggle' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1901181294 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1901181294 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At 1415 today, Zionist warplanes raided bases that 
belong to the Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine-General Command [PFLP-GC] in the Bi'wirta region. The 
bases have been used for over a year as centers for social and 
medical services. 
  A spokesman for the PFLP-GC has made the following 
statement: 
At exactly 1415 today, a formation of Zionist warplanes raided 
al-Na'imah region targeting a dispensary that belongs to the 
PFLP-GC and firing several missiles. Two workers in the 
dispensary sustained various injuries. Also, the dispensary 
building, in addition to several cars and surrounding buildings, 
sustained material damage. One of the two workers was died from 
his injury. 
  Until the early hours of the evening, the Zionist enemy 
planes conducted reconnaissance missions over the region. Boat 
lights were also spotted off the al-Damur and al-Na'imah coasts. 
  The spokesman added that the PFLP-GC, which was targeted by 
Zionist shelling for the second time in two weeks, declares that 
these strikes will only increase its resolve and strengthen its 
refusal to make peace with or recognize the Zionist enemy. It 
will continue to support the popular intifadah in Palestine 
until the defeat of the treasonous Gaza-Jericho agreement. 
  The PFLP-GC reasserts that it will continue to adhere to 
armed struggle and jihad, in addition to national and Islamic 
resistance in southern Lebanon and Palestine, until the 
liberation of Palestine and all of the occupied Arab territories. 
  It is a revolution until the liberation of man and land. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

