<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jibril: Al-Asad Foiled U.S. Bid To Impose Autonomy Deal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2001213394 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2001213394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Paris] Radio Monte Carlo has reported that Ahmad 
Jibril, secretary general of the Popular Front for the 
Liberation of Palestine-General Command [PFLP-GC], has accused 
the U.S. Administration of deception, disinformation, and 
hypocrisy in its attempts to cause dissension among the allies 
opposing the Palestinian limited self-rule agreement. Jibril, 
who was speaking to AFP, continued: The objective that 
Washington sought to achieve through the Geneva summit was to 
neutralize the Syrian position so it could impose the 
Gaza-Jericho First agreement. However, the strength and 
firmness of the President al-Asad's position has foiled this 
objective. President al-Asad stood in defense of the Arab 
nation's causes and refuted all allegations. In Geneva, 
President al-Asad was as we have always known him -- an Arab 
knight faithful to the Arab nation's rights. 

</TEXT>

