<H3> <TI>   Al-Jihad's Al-Zumur Offers Deal To Stop Bloodshed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901170394 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 12 Jan 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> NC1901170394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report from the "36 News Items" section of the </F>
"Political Week" page] 
  [Text] 'Abbud al-Zumur [leader of al-Jihad's military wing] 
has renewed an offer he made earlier to the Ministry of 
Interior. He is willing to help stop the bloodshed involving the 
police and the Islamic organizations and the operations against 
tourism in return for improving the treatment of inmates and 
releasing a number of the detained [Islamic] leaders. 
  Information affirms that the security sections have 
described 
the offer as an individual initiative not worth pursuing, 
particularly after the Islamic Group has announced that al-Zumur 
has joined its ranks and relinquished his leadership of one 
faction of the al-Jihad Organization. 

</TEXT>

