<H3> <TI>   Guinean Foreign Minister Sylla Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901160794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1457 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1901160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 19 Jan (MENA)--Guinean Foreign Minister 
Ibrahima Sylla arrived in Cairo this afternoon on a visit that 
will last for several days. The Guinean minister will deliver a 
message to President Mubarak from Guinean President General 
Lansana Conte. 
  On his arrival the Guinean minister said that he will brief 
President Mubarak, in his capacity as OAU chairman, on the 
results of the elections that were held in Guinea on 17 December. 
  He praised relations between Guinea and his country, noting 
that his visit presents an opportunity to develop them further. 
He added that he will discuss issues of common interest with 
Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa. 

</TEXT>

