<H3> <TI>   Musa Comments on Relations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2001142394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1120 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2001142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 Jan (MENA)--After President Mubarak 
received Guinean Foreign Minister Ibrahima Sylla today, Foreign 
Minister 'Amr Musa stated today that Mubarak handed Sylla a 
message answering the Guinean president. The foreign minister 
said bilateral relations between the two countries will 
continue, especially in light of recent developments in Guinea 
after presidential and legislative elections. 
  Guinean Foreign Minister Ibrahima Sylla stated that 
President 
Mubarak, in his capacity as current president of the OAU, is 
very concerned about all conflicts in the region. 
  He added that Guinean President Lansana Conte asked him to 
inform President Mubarak on the conflicts in that part of 
Africa, especially the problem in Liberia, which has started 
moving toward a solution. 
  The Guinean foreign minister praised Egypt's extensive 
diplomatic activity on Middle Eastern and African problems. He 
noted that he exchanged opinions with 'Amr Musa on the situation 
in the Middle East and Africa and other issues in the 
international arena. 

</TEXT>

