<H3> <TI>   Musa Receives New Argentine Ambassador </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901142394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1330 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1901142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 19 Jan (MENA)--New Argentine Ambassador in 
Cairo Albino Gomez has voiced his country's support of Egypt's 
effort to boost the Middle East peace process and find a 
comprehensive settlement. In a statement today, the ambassador 
said his country has always backed efforts to find a peaceful 
solution to this crisis. 
  Gomez praised Egyptian-Argentine relations, adding that his 
country is eager to consolidate and develop these relations. 
  The ambassador was speaking after a meeting with Foreign 
Minister 'Amr Musa, who received a copy of the ambassador's 
credentials. 

</TEXT>

