<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Assails `Campaign' Against Khartoum, Iran </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001144494 Tehran IRNA in English 1358 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2001144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, Jan. 20, IRNA -- Sudan's first deputy 
foreign minister, 'Umar Berido [name as received], here Thursday 
termed as baseless the smear campaign launched by the global 
arrogance both against Khartoum and Tehran to portray them as 
terorrists. 
  Interviewed by IRNA, Berido said that economic and political 
stability in Iran and Sudan prompted the global arrogance to 
make such accusations. He stressed that the global arrogance 
which attributed terorristic activities to Iran and Sudan has 
remained silent towards atrocities being committed against 
Muslims in Palestine and Bosnia-Herzegovina. Berido said that 
definitely the two countries will overcome the difficulties with 
the help of God. 
  Commenting on Tehran-Khartoum relations, the Sudanese 
official said bilateral ties enjoy special sigfnificance and are 
deep and friendly. 

</TEXT>

