<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   14-16 Jan Air `Violations' Protested to Arab League </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2001114594 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1042 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2001114594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 Jan (INA)--Iraq has once again protested 
to the Arab League over the continued violations of the Iraqi 
airspace by U.S., British, and French aircraft, which are 
provided with facilities by the rulers of Saudi Arabia and 
Kuwait. These violations pose a grave threat to Iraq's 
security, stability, and national unity. 
  In a letter to Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 
'Abd-al- Majid, Iraq's permanent envoy said on 14, 15, and 16 
January, these aircraft continued their violations of the Iraqi 
airspace and conducted 129 hostile sorties by flying from bases 
in Saudi Arabia and Kuwait. 
  The Iraqi envoy asked that the letter be distributed to the 
Arab member states. A list detailing these violations was 
enclosed. 

</TEXT>

