<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Diversification in Defense Production Stressed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1901162694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1901162694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister has stressed on diversification 
by the defense public sector undertakings without, in any way, 
impairing their primary role of serving the country's armed 
forces. Addressing the members of the Parliamentary 
Consultative Committee attached to the Defense Ministry in New 
Delhi, Mr. P.V. Narasimha Rao said the motivation for 
diversification in defense production units does not mean any 
reduction in defense production, but aims at increasing their 
turnover and exposing them to commercial culture. It was 
disclosed in the meeting that as part of the diversification 
drive during 1993-94, 22 percent of the sales of the ordnance 
factories are expected to be to nondefense customers. 
  The chief of the Army Staff, General B.C. Joshi, informed 
the 
committee of the Army's decision to induct the indigenous main 
battle tank Arjun in its fold. Expressing full faith in the 
capability of the tank, General Joshi said it meets all the 
requirements of the Army. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

