<H3> <TI>   IDF Reports Air Attack Against `Terrorist' Target </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1901134694 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1330 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1901134694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This afternoon, Israel Air Force jets attacked a 
terrorist target in al-Na'imah in south Lebanon. The target 
belonged to Ahmad Jibril's Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine-General Command [PFLP-GC]. 
  An IDF [Israel Defense Forces] spokesman said that the 
pilots 
reported accurate hits against the target. All our planes 
returned safely to base. The target that was hit served as a 
training base for the PFLP--GC. 

