<H3> <TI>   Beirut Radio on Air Raid, Shelling </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901142894 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1400 GMT 19 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1901142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A military source has said that Israeli warplanes 
carried out an air raid on the al-Na'imah hills at 1430 today 
and that Lebanese Army antiaircraft guns stationed in the area 
confronted them. Our correspondent reports that an Israeli 
plane fired a missile at the headquarters of the Ahmad 
Jibril-led Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine--General Command in the al-Na'imah hills at 1430. The 
extent of the damage is not yet known. 
  Shortly before 1445 today, the Iqlim al-Tuffah hills came 
under artillery bombardment originating from the Israeli 
occupation forces' positions in Sujud, Bi'r Kallab, Mlita, and 
al-Luwayzah. The shelling coincided with raking by large-caliber 
machine guns. 
  A resistance group today carried out a machine-gun and 
rocket 
attack on the Sujud position, where the resistance and the 
occupation forces clashed for 10 minutes. 

