<H3> <TI>   1 Killed in Air Raid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901173694 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 19 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1901173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] At 1430 today Israeli military planes carried 
out a raid on the headquarters of the Popular Front for the 
Liberation of Palestine-General Command [PFLP-GC] in the 
al-Na'imah hills. The Lebanese Army's ground resistance 
confronted the planes. The raid left one man dead and another 
wounded. 
  A Lebanese Army source told the NATIONAL NEWS AGENCY that 
two 
Israeli planes flew over the al-Na'imah hills and fired a 
missile at the position. The source said that the Lebanese Army 
confronted the raiding planes with antiaircraft fire. [passage 
omitted] 
  A PFLP-GC spokesman told AFP that a PFLP-GC member was 
killed 
while on the way to the hospital and another was seriously 
injured in the raid. The spokesman pointed out that the raid 
targeted a clinic run by the PFLP-GC. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-53943 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes014_n_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-014 </AU>
