<H3> <TI>   U.S. Gives Invitation for Washington Peace Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2001195994 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 20 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2001195994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Ministry Secretary General Zafir al-Hasan 
received from U.S. Ambassador Mark Hambley today an invitation 
for Lebanon to attend the bilateral peace negotiations that will 
be resumed in Washington next week. 
  After the meeting, Hambley announced that the heads of the 
Arab and Israeli delegations will meet on 24 January to make 
preparations for a new round of talks. No specific date for the 
beginning of the talks has yet been set. 
  Hambley noted the positive atmosphere created by the 
U.S.-Syrian summit and said he hopes that progress will be made 
on the Syrian and Lebanese negotiating tracks. 
  In answer to a question, the U.S. ambassador said the 
withdrawal of foreign forces from Lebanese territory is one of 
the most important tenets of U.S. policy in Lebanon, which 
endorses the substance of UN Security Council Resolution 425. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

