<H3> <TI>   `Unfriendly Attitude' Denounced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101093394 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 0900 
GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101093394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern Swiss Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Iran has denounced what it calls Switzerland's 
unfriendly attitude following a series of disputes which have 
soured relations between the two countries. 
  The Iranian ambassador in Bern, Mohammad Reza Alborzi, said 
his Swiss counterpart in Tehran was summoned to the Iranian 
Foreign Ministry on Wednesday [19 January] to explain 
Switzerland's position. 
  The ambassador was speaking after the Swiss Broadcasting 
Corporation suspended a cooperation agreement with Iranian 
Television. The move follows reports that Iranian Television 
was used as a front by people involved in the assassination 
three years ago of a former Iranian prime minister, Shahpur 
Bakhtiyar. 

</TEXT>

