<H3> <TI>   Hizballah of Iraq Congress Opens in Tehran </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001121594 Tehran IRNA in English 1124 Griffin </F>
<F P=103> LD2001121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Jan 20, IRNA -- The fourth congress of 
Hizballah of Iraq opened here Thursday on the fourth martyrdom 
anniversary of Iraq's prominent clergyman Hojatoleslam Mahdi 
Hakim. 
  The congress is attended by a number of distinguished Iraqi 
political and religious figures who are to assess the present 
situation in Iraq and ways to help the Iraqi people. 
  Addressing the session, head of the congress Shaykh Asad 
Silli, said that the objective is to discuss the latest 
developments in Iraq, propose ways of consolidating ranks of the 
Iraqi opposition and mobilize all resources to support the Iraqi 
oppressed people. 

</TEXT>

