<H3> <TI>   Peres Departs for Oslo, To Meet With 'Arafat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2101081094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 21 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2101081094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres says the 
disagreements between Israel and the PLO lie in the sphere of 
security, including control of border crossings, road security, 
and the size of security areas. Mr. Peres says that to bridge 
these gaps, Israel is prepared to view new proposals, provided 
they are in line with Israel's security concepts. 
  The foreign minister made these remarks to our political 
correspondent Shlomo Raz prior to his departure for Oslo, where 
he will meet with U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher and 
PLO head Yasir 'Arafat and attend the funeral of Norwegian 
Foreign Minister Johan Jorgen Holst. 

</TEXT>

