<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres: Referendum Will Not Tie Government's Hands </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2001153994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 20 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2001153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres said that a national 
referendum on the Golan Heights would not prevent the government 
from reaching a decision on the issue, nor would it tie the 
government's hands in the negotiations. When asked whether or 
not he was in favor of a national referendum, Peres replied: We 
will decide at the appropriate time. I am not rejecting the 
idea out of hand. The foreign minister was speaking at Bet Berl 
during a ceremony in which scholarships were awarded to Jewish 
and Arab students. 

</TEXT>

