<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabinovich: Next Talks With Syria `Closed' to Media </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2001211594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 2100 GMT 20 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2001211594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ambassador Itamar Rabinovich, the head of the 
Israeli delegation to the negotiations with Syria, said that the 
next round of talks scheduled to resume next week would be held 
behind closed doors and far away from the media. Ambassador 
Rabinovich also told reporters in Washington that a national 
referendum would force Syria to take Israeli public opinion into 
account because voters would not support any kind of withdrawal 
unless they were certain of getting real peace in exchange. 
  The message to the Syrians was that they would have to do 
more if they wanted Israeli society and Israel's political 
establishment to meet them half way, Itamar Rabinovich explained. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

