<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister on Possibility of Full Golan Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2001191194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1800 GMT 20 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2001191194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Outside the Labor Bureau 
meeting, Housing Minister Binyamin Ben-Eli'ezer, who is close to 
Rabin, said if al-Asad would do what the late Egyptian President 
al-Sadat did, 16 years ago, he might discover that Israel is 
willing to withdraw completely from the Golan Heights. 
  [Begin Ben-Eli'ezer recording] With all the problems that 
we had with Egypt, once President al-Sadat came to the 
parliament of Israel and made his declaration -- once he stated: 
No more war. -- I think he did 70 percent out of the problem 
[as heard]. He had convinced the Israeli people. If President 
al-Asad will do the same, maybe. He might be surprised and get 
maybe the same thing. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

