<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman `Informal' Papers Handed to India </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1901162294 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 
1600 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1901162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has handed over two informal papers to the 
Indian high commissioner in Islamabad containing ideas and 
proposals to take measures required for solution of Jammu and 
Kashmir problem and other issues. These papers have also been 
given by the Pakistani high commissioner in New Delhi to the 
Indian foreign secretary. One of the informal papers comprised 
modalities for holding a plebiscite in Jammu and Kashmir. He 
[as heard] said Pakistan -- with a view to extending informal 
ideas and proposals in developing future useful discussion on 
Jammu and Kashmir problem -- has sent these informal papers to 
India. 
  Replying to a question, the spokesman made it clear that 
giving informal papers does not mean that Pakistan has proposed 
any schedule for next round of Pakistan-India talks. 

</TEXT>

