<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO To Participate in Washington Peace Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2001194194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1830 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2001194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 20 Jan (MENA)--PLO Executive Committee member 
Samir Ghawshah has announced that the committee has decided to 
take part in the next round of the bilateral peace talks, due to 
begin in Washington on Monday [24 January]. 
  In a statement to the MENA correspondent in Tunis, he said 
the Palestinian leadership is holding contacts with Dr. Haydar 
'Abd-al-Shafi to lead the Palestinian delegation to these talks. 
If he refuses, Ghawshah added, Dr. Sa'ib 'Urayqat, the deputy 
head of the delegation, will lead the delegation in the next 
round. 
  Ghawshah emphasized the importance of coordination and 
cooperation among all Arab parties taking part in the peace 
talks, as was the case before the signing of the Declaration of 
Principles between the PLO and Israel on 13 September. 
  He said the positive results of the summit held between U.S. 
President Bill Clinton and Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad will 
have a positive effect on all tracks and will advance the peace 
process. He added that the summit results will also have a 
positive effect on the Palestinians. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

