<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Asad's Son Basil Killed in `Tragic Accident' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2101135194 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1320 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2101135194 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unscheduled announcement] </F>
  [Text] In the name of God, the merciful, the compassionate. 
To the righteous soul will be said: O thou soul, in complete 
rest and satisfaction! Come back thou to Thy Lord, well-pleased 
thyself, and well-pleasing unto Him. Enter thou, then, among my 
devotees! Yea, enter thou my heaven! [Koranic verses] 
  With resignation to God's will, and with immense sorrow and 
sadness, President Hafiz al-Asad announces to the people the 
death of his lost one, which is a loss to the dear homeland, 
Staff Major and Engineer Paratrooper Basil al-Asad, who passed 
away on the morning of Friday, 10 Sha'ban 1414 Hegira, 
corresponding to 21 January 1994, as a result of a tragic 
accident. His pure body will be laid to rest in al-Qardahah 
after the noon prayers on Saturday 11 Sha'ban 1414 Hegira, 
corresponding to 22 January 1994. 
  From God we come and to Him we return. 

</TEXT>

