<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Expresses `Satisfaction' With Summit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2001114694 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 19 Jan 94 p3 </F>
<F P=103> PM2001114694 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Salwa al-Ustuwani report from Damascus and unattributed </F>
AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT report from Amman: "Palestinian Opposition 
Organizations Express Satisfaction With Summit Results"] 
  [Text] The Palestinians in Damascus have expressed general 
satisfaction with the U.S.-Syrian summit results. They saw 
President Hafiz al-Asad's Geneva declaration of insistence on a 
comprehensive solution on all fronts and on the UN Security 
Council resolutions as significant and positive for the peace 
process. 
  Dawud al-Talhami, member of the Political Bureau of the 
Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP] and its 
official spokesman, has told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that the emphasis 
on a comprehensive solution and rejection of partial and 
separate solutions was a positive sign particularly as such 
emphasis also came from the United States. He added that 
although there were no details and we still do not know what 
happened at the summit, for that will become clear in the 
future, what was emphatically stated by President Hafiz al-Asad 
calls for Palestinian satisfaction, particularly the insistence 
on a comprehensive solution, implementation of Resolutions 242, 
338, and 425, and the land-for-peace principle. Al-Talhami also 
said that what was stated by President al-Asad and supported by 
U.S. President Bill Clinton was positive and represented the 
essence of the position we adopt and whose fulfillment we desire. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

