<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Spy Network' Said Working for Mosad in Gaza </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1901145094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 18 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1901145094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Muhammad 'Ali al-Qulaybi report: "Palestinian Spy Network </F>
for Mosad in Gaza"] 
  [Text] Tunis -- The PLO has managed to unravel the clues 
to recent assassination operations in the Gaza Strip which 
claimed the lives of three of its most prominent leaders in the 
strip: Lawyer Abu-Sha'ban, As'ad al-Saftawi, and Mahmud Kahil. 
  Investigations have revealed that a Palestinian spy network 
worked for the Israeli intelligence service Mosad in Gaza. 
  Palestinian security services inside discovered during their 
two-month investigations that this network received orders from 
Mosad to begin the assassination scheme. The security services 
managed to unravel the clues and enticed one of those implicated 
to go to Tunis at the end of last week. 
  This Palestinian is named as Ahmad Abu-'Awf, a resident of 
Khan Yunus. He is 24. He was enticed to go Tunis after 
visiting his brother in London. 
  Palestinian security services kept silent about this case to 
ensure that other members of the network would not escape. 
According to AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT's information, a committee has 
been formed from the inside and outside to follow up this 
delicate case. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

