<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Several Parties To Participate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401024294 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2300 
GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401024294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Less than 36 hours before the convening of the 
national conference, a number of political parties that have 
weight in the political arena have announced that they would 
boycott the conference. Meanwhile some parties, mass and 
vocational organizations, have announced that they would 
participate. Others will remain in a state of anticipation and 
waiting until Monday morning before deciding on their final 
stance regarding participation, including the Islamic al-Nahdah 
Movement, whose leader Abdallah Djaballah said on 23 January 
that the official decision would be announced 24 January. 
[passage omitted] 
  Among the parties that have declared their intention to 
participate are the National Democratic Socialist Party, which 
yesterday called for unity to ensure the success of the national 
conference and confirmed its intention to participate in it. 
[passage omitted] 
  The Algerian Party for Justice and Progress yesterday 
confirmed its intention to participate in the national 
conference and called on all the political parties to ensure the 
success of the national consensus conference. 
  At the end of its emergency session, the national council of 
the national organization of war veterans announced the 
organization's intention to participate in the national 
conference. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

