<H3> <TI>   Three Parties Plan Boycott </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201230694 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2201230694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The National Liberation Front is the third party so 
far to announce its boycott of the national conference; the 
Socialist Forces Front was the first party to announce its 
boycott which was followed by the Workers Party [WP], which is 
led by Mrs. Louisa Hannoun, whose Central Committee has decided, 
following an emergency meeting held during the last two days, to 
boycott the national conference. In a statement received today 
by the Algerian Press Service, Mrs. Louisa Hannoun, WP's leader, 
pointed out that her party refuses to take part in the 
conference because the state of emergency still exists, 
political prisoners continue to be detained, and democratic 
freedoms continue to be absent. 

</TEXT>

