<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Scholars Group Denies TAJ Links </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201154694 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1200 
GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2201154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Two days after its meeting in Harcha Hall [Algiers], 
the Conference of Scholars issued a clarifying statement signed 
by figures from the provisional body including Mahfouz Nahnah 
and Boujerra Soltani. 
  The clarification concerns the address of Cheikh Mahfouz 
Nahnah in which he announced his intention to set up the Islamic 
Republican Rally, [TAJ] [crown]. 
  The clarifying statement said that there was no link between 
the Conference of Scholars and its provisional body with what is 
called TAJ or with any other organization. The statement added 
that the body, which the Conference of Scholars intends to set 
up, has not yet been announced and is under study. 
  The Conference of Scholars is a body that conforms to 
Islamic 
law and is independent from all parties, organizations, and 
official quarters. The statement also said that the aim of this 
body is to enlighten public opinion with the view of Islamic 
jurisdiction on the major issues of the nation in cooperation 
with experts, scholars, and preachers, in order to unite the 
word of the nation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

