<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO's Yasir 'Arafat Arrives in Cairo on Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2301071894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0617 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2301071894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 23 Jan (MENA)--Palestinian president Yasir 
'Arafat arrived in Cairo early this morning on a short visit to 
Egypt. 
  'Arafat said in an arrival statement that he will brief 
President Husni Mubarak on the results of his meeting with 
Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres in Oslo. 
  'Arafat emphasized the importance of persistence to reach an 
agreement with Israel for the meticulous implementation of the 
Declaration of Principles, which was signed in Washington on 13 
September. 
  He said that there are many obstacles that have prevented 
the 
implementation of the agreement until now. We expect the 
Palestinian-Israeli talks to continue to overcome the obstacles, 
he added. 'Arafat said that he is hoping that President Mubarak 
will make efforts to remove these obstacles. 
  He noted that he will pay a visit to Saudi Arabia today to 
perform a mini-pilgrimage and meet with Saudi officials. 

</TEXT>

