<H3> <TI>   Mubarak Sends Condolence Cable to Syria's al-Asad </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2101195594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1930 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2101195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 21 Jan (MENA)--President Husni Mubarak has 
sent a cable of condolences to Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad 
upon the death of his son Staff Major Basil al-Asad, who passed 
away today. The following is the text of the cable: 
  Dear brother Your Excellency Hafiz al-Asad, president of the 
Syrian Arab Republic: 
  With deep sorrow and extreme grief I have received the news 
of the death of your son [words indistinct]. While sympathizing 
with you over this tragic incident, I pray God Almighty to have 
mercy on the dear deceased, may he rest in Paradise, and grant 
you and all the members of your family patience and consolation. 
From God we came and to Him we return. 

</TEXT>

