<H3> <TI>   Police Arrest 200 Suspected Criminals in Cairo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2301095894 Cairo MENA in English 0838 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2301095894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, Jan 23 (MENA)--Different police units this 
morning encircled and combed different randomly built areas in 
east of Cairo within the context of a new strategy drawn up by 
the Interior Ministry to uproot all that could compromise the 
stability and security, Major General Mahmud Wadi, head of the 
General Police Investigation Department, said. 
  Some 200 suspects involved in criminal and political 
wrongdoings were arrested during these campaigns. 
  It was discovered that two among them had received death 
sentences while in absentia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

