<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former Opposition Official Returns to Country </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2301174394 Khartoum SUNA in English 1015 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2301174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 23 Jan (SUNA) -- The former secretary 
general of Anyanya Two Movement, Ben Lail Mendeng [name as 
received], returned home Saturday [22 January] from abroad, 
ending years he spent at the ranks of the so-called Sudanese 
opposition abroad. 
  Mendeng was received following his return by the secretary 
general of the council for International People's Friendship, 
Dr. Mustafa 'Uthman Isma'il, welcoming him home and explaining 
that the opposition abroad has fallen at the hands of forces 
that do not want to see peace prevail in the Sudan. 

</TEXT>

