<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Views Cease-Fire with Hekmatyar, Dostam </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2301105894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0945 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2301105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kabul, 23 Jan (MENA)--Afghan President Borhanoddin 
Rabbani has accused foreign powers of taking part in the 
abortive coup carried out against him on 1 January. 
  In an exclusive statement given to a MENA correspondent in 
Kabul, Rabbani reiterated that foreign powers planned and 
financed the conspiracy to achieve special covetous designs, 
although Afghanistan does not interfere in their affairs. The 
Afghan president said that the coup attempt was a vicious plot 
perpetrated by Golboddin Hekmatyar, General Abdul Rashid Dostam, 
the communists, and other parties in a bid to overthrow the 
Islamic regime in Kabul by armed force. He pointed out that 
they planned to execute the plot on the anniversary of the 
foundation of the Communist Party in Afghanistan. 
  The Afghan president described Gen. Dostam as a professional 
killer and a traitor. He said that Dostam is a remnant of the 
former communist regime. The Afghan president added that 
Golboddin Hekmatyar has distorted the image of jihad and 
mojahedin in Afghanistan. After the inception of the Islamic 
state in Afghanistan, we granted them amnesty with the hope that 
they would repent and contribute toward reconstructing a new 
Afghanistan, the Afghan president added. But, driven by their 
criminal nature, they decided to return to their conspiratorial 
course. 
  President Borhanoddin Rabbani noted that all Muslim 
scholars, 
shayks, mojahedin leaders, and Islamic political powers had 
responded to the Islamic jihad call. The Afghan president 
revealed that many mojahedin leaders, who belong to Hekmatyar 
groups, refused to take part in the coup attempt and rejected 
his alliance with Dostam. 
  Rabbani said that he will reject any contacts for a 
cease-fire with Dostam, but he added that it is possible to work 
out a kind of cease-fire formula with Hekmatyar provided there 
are guarantees that he would not violate it. The Afghan 
president stressed that the Afghan people are capable of 
crushing any domestic rebellion or foreign plot. The Afghan 
people will continue to support their Islamic state with all 
their strength, President Rabbani added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

