<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council Welcomes Mediation Efforts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2301084494 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service in 
English 0800 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2301084494 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Overseas Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Afghan prime minister, Mr. Golboddin Hekmatyar, 
has said the Supreme Coordination Council representing the 
parties opposed to President Rabbani will welcome mediation 
efforts by any country, including Pakistan for the restoration 
of peace in Kabul. This was stated by a spokesman of Hezb-e 
Eslami [Islamic Party of Afghanistan], while talking to Radio 
Pakistan's representative in Peshawar this morning. He urged 
President Rabbani to accept cease-fire offer of 45-group of 
mojahedin commanders to pave the way for a dialogue to end the 
fighting in Afghanistan. 
  Reports from Afghanistan say Kabul was relatively calm this 
morning barring a few minor skirmishes. 

</TEXT>

