<H3> <TI>   Arab League Notified of 17-20 Jan Air `Violations' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2401101294 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0820 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2401101294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 24 Jan (INA)--Iraq has again notified the 
Arab League of the continued provision of facilities by the 
rulers of Kuwait and Saudi Arabia for the U.S. British, and 
French aircraft that violate Iraqi airspace and threaten its 
security, sovereignty, and national unity. 
  In a letter, Iraq's permanent representative to the Arab 
League said that U.S., British, and French aircraft continued to 
violate Iraqi airspace on 17, 18, 19, and 20 January. After 
taking off from bases in Saudi Arabia and Kuwait, the aircraft 
carried out 202 hostile air sorties. 
  A list detailing these violations has been attached to the 
letter. 

</TEXT>

