<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Abd-al-Majid Attends Agriculture Meeting in Syria </TI></H3>
<H4>   Comments on Arab Boycott </H4>
<F P=102> NC2101162994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1512 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2101162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 21 Jan (MENA)--Arab League Secretary General 
Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid left Cairo for Damascus yesterday on a 
four-day visit to Syria during which he will attend a two-day 
meeting of the Arab Organization for Agricultural Development 
that will begin tomorrow, Saturday. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid said that this visit will be a good 
opportunity to confer with Syrian officials. He emphasized that 
current important developments make such exchanges of views 
necessary. 
  'Abd-al-Majid said he met with U.S. Commerce Secretary 
Ronald 
Brown yesterday, Thursday, and discussed with him several issues 
connected with the peace process, regional economic cooperation, 
and the Arab boycott of Israel. 
  Asked if agreement was reached during his meeting with the 
U.S. commerce secretary to end this boycott, Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid 
announced that the direct boycott will not be ended because the 
reasons for it still exist. He said he hoped these factors will 
soon disappear. 
  He added that what happened was that the U.S. secretary of 
commerce asked him to consider the possibility of terminating 
the indirect Arab boycott of Israel in view of its effect on a 
large number of U.S. companies which are being boycotted by the 
Arab countries because they deal with Israel. 

</TEXT>

