<H3> <TI>   Joint Naval Exercises With Italy Begin in Gulf </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2301114794 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1100 GMT 
23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2301114794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Joint Italian-Kuwaiti naval maneuvers have begun in 
Kuwaiti waters in the Gulf, northeast of the island of Kubbar. 
They are aimed at training the Navy of the emirate in the 
defense of the shores and, in particular, of the oil plants. 
  The exercise will last two days; 600 sailors of both 
countries will participate. The frigate "Sagittario", the 
corvette "Urania" and 330 men--sailors and officers--will 
represent Italy. 
  Firing practice with real shells is scheduled. 

