<H3> <TI>   `High-Ranking' Iranian Delegation Arrives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201173794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2201173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Interior Minister Besharati arrived in Doha, the 
capital of Qatar, this morning at the head of a high-ranking 
political-economic delegation. During the first round of talks, 
the Qatari interior minister described Besharati's visit to 
Qatar as an indication of the importance the Islamic Republic of 
Iran attaches to the expansion and consolidation of relations 
with Qatar, adding: We must not allow certain impure hands to 
throw a wrench in the good relations between the two countries. 
He declared his country's full readiness to expand relations 
between the two countries in the political, security, economic, 
and commercial fields and in the battle against narcotics. He 
expressed the wish to benefit from the Islamic Republic of 
Iran's experience in combating narcotics. 
  Besharati, for his part, referred to the good ties between 
Iran and Qatar and expressed the Islamic Republic of Iran's 
readiness to cooperate with Qatar and neighboring countries in 
various fields. 

</TEXT>

