<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Qatar </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranian Stresses Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2301115994 Tehran IRNA in English 1143 GMT 23 GMT 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2301115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Jan. 23, IRNA -- Iran's Interior Minister 
'Ali Mohammad Besharati underlined the importance of cooperation 
among the Persian Gulf countries as a guarantee of maintaining 
security in the region. 
  Speaking to reporters in Doha on Saturday [22 January], he 
said Iran as a powerful country which plays a major role in 
preservation of security and tranquility in the region, is ready 
to cooperate with regional countries. 
  He stressed that withdrawal of foreign forces and fleet from 
the Persian Gulf waters not only would not harm security in the 
region but would rather reinforce it. 
  Referring to Iran-UAE dispute, Besharati said the two 
neighbors could settle their dispute over one of the Persian 
Gulf islands through negotiations and remarked that Iran had 
repeatedly voiced readiness in this connection. 
  He further noted that interference of foreign countries 
should not be interpreted as their concern for security, adding 
that Iran would never interfere in the affairs of regional 
countries. 
  On fabrications made by some western media on human rights 
violation in Iran, the minister said those in fact were 
supporting terrorists who were involved in the massacre of many 
Iranian senior officials and civilians. 
  He regretted fratricide in Afghanistan and noted that Iran, 
like other Muslim countries, had made diplomatic efforts to 
establish peace and tranquility in that country and assured that 
the dispute could be solved through negotiations. 

</TEXT>

