<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Saudi Arabia </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Reportedly To Apologize for War Stand </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2301182594 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 23 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2301182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Dispatch by 'Abdallah al-Shihri from Riyadh] </F>
  [Text] PLO Executive Committee Chairman Yasir 'Arafat is 
expected to arrive in Jeddah tonight on the first visit to Saudi 
Arabia since the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait in August 1990. 
'Arafat, who will perform the minor pilgrimage, will be 
accompanied by a delegation which comprises Ahmad Quray', also 
known as Abu-'Ala', head of the PLO Economic Department, and 
Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, head of the PLO Information Department. 
Informed sources said that 'Arafat will head for Riyadh 
tomorrow to meet with King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz and senior 
Saudi officials. 
  Reliable sources said that 'Arafat will offer an official 
apology to the Saudi monarch for his stands during the Gulf war. 
'Arafat will also discuss with the custodian of the two holy 
mosques the developments in the Palestinian-Israeli accord on 
self-rule in the occupied territories, particularly following 
the Oslo meeting between 'Arafat and Peres, and the results of 
the summit meeting between Presidents Bill Clinton and Hafiz 
al-Asad as well as its repercussions on the peace process in the 
region. 
  'Arafat said in an arrival statement in Cairo this morning 
that he will meet with some Saudi officials to discuss the 
latest developments in the peace process. Hakam Bal'awi, the 
Palestinian ambassador in Tunis, said -- following his meeting 
Friday with the Saudi ambassador in Tunis -- that 'Arafat's 
meeting with King Fahd will strengthen Saudi-Palestinian 
relations as well as Arab solidarity. 

</TEXT>

