<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Indonesian Foreign Minister Alatas Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2401100594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2401100594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Indonesian Foreign Minister brother Ali Alatas and 
his delegation arrived in Sanaa last night on a short visit to 
our country. During the visit, he will meet with brother 
officials at the Foreign Ministry and the Planning and 
Development Ministry, as well as senior state officials. In a 
statement to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA, Alatas said that he 
and his delegation are pleased to visit our country. He 
indicated the deep-rooted, historical relations between the 
Yemeni and Indonesian peoples, particularly [words indistinct] 
the tolerant Islamic faith. He said that many Indonesian 
citizens are descended from Yemeni origins, and that he takes 
pride in his Yemeni roots. 
  He was welcomed by Foreign Minister brother Muhammad Salim 
Basindawa, a number of brother officials, and the Indonesian 
ambassador and embassy staff. 

</TEXT>

