<H3> <TI>   King Fahd Sends Condolences to Syria's al-Asad </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101201894 Riyadh SPA in English 1942 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2101201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riyadh, Jan 21, SPA -- The Custodian of the Two Holy 
Mosques King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz condoled, in a telephone 
call, Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad over the sad demise of his 
eldest son Basil al-Asad. King Fahd prayed to Allah almighty to 
bestow his mercy on the deceased and to grant his bereaved 
family patience and solace. Basil, 31, an army major, engineer 
and parachutist, died on Friday in a car crash. 

</TEXT>

